🔹 Weak Law of Large Numbers

Probability that sample mean deviates from μ becomes very small.

🔹 Strong Law of Large Numbers

Sample mean converges to μ almost surely.

📌 GATE mostly focuses on concept, not proof.

🔹 Central Limit Theorem (CLT)

One of the most important results in statistics.

It states:

The sum (or average) of many independent random variables tends toward a normal distribution.

